---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy · Policy Wonk"
  description="What Policy Wonk stores, what it doesn't, and how to delete your account."
  zone="notes"
>
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-8 prose-style">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-2">Policy Wonk</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold leading-tight">Privacy</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-text-soft)]">
        Short version: the game works without an account. If you sign in, we keep your email,
        nickname, avatar, and play history so you can revise the topics you missed. Nothing else.
        No tracking cookies, no cross-site tracking, no selling your data. We do measure
        aggregate, anonymous usage to see what's working — never anything that identifies you.
        This page spells out what that means.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">What we store</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-base leading-relaxed">
        <li><strong>Your email address.</strong> Used only to send you the one-time sign-in link and to recognise your account when you come back.</li>
        <li><strong>Your nickname and avatar.</strong> The display name and pixel-art icon you picked at signup. Shown on shared scores and in your play history.</li>
        <li><strong>Your play history.</strong> One row per finished game: which module, when, your score, the outcome (won / lost / walked away), and which lifelines you used. This is what drives the per-module notes unlock and your score history.</li>
        <li><strong>A signed session cookie.</strong> A small token that tells the site you're logged in. It expires after 30 days of inactivity and is never read by anyone else's site.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">What we don't store</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-base leading-relaxed">
        <li>Tracking cookies or cross-site identifiers. No Google Analytics, no Facebook pixel, no Mixpanel, no ad networks. The analytics we <em>do</em> use (see below) are cookieless and anonymous, so there's no cookie banner.</li>
        <li>Behavioural profiling. The only third-party scripts are Google's font CDN and Cloudflare's cookieless Web Analytics beacon — neither builds a profile of you or follows you across the web.</li>
        <li>Your IP address, beyond the short-term cache used to rate-limit sign-in emails. That cache resets after 15 minutes and is never written to disk.</li>
        <li>Anything we'd share with, sell to, or give to anyone outside the project. We don't have advertisers, partners, or data deals.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">What we measure</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-3">
        To see what's working and what to fix, we measure usage in two ways — both
        anonymous and aggregate. Neither uses cookies, so there's no cookie banner, and
        neither can tell who you are or whether you've played before.
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-base leading-relaxed">
        <li><strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics.</strong> Cloudflare (the service that hosts this site) counts page views and visits and notes rough referrer, country, and device type. It's cookieless, doesn't fingerprint your browser, and doesn't store your IP address.</li>
        <li><strong>First-party gameplay events.</strong> When a game starts and finishes, we record the module, the outcome (won / lost / walked away), and the score to our own Cloudflare Analytics Engine. No name, email, IP, or account id is attached — just anonymous counts that tell us which modules get played and finished.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Who can see your account data</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
        The admin (Aasif) can view your email, nickname, avatar, and play history for
        troubleshooting and to improve the game. No one else has access. There is no
        team, no third-party processor, and no shared dashboard.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">How long we keep it</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-base leading-relaxed">
        <li><strong>Account data</strong> — until you ask us to delete it. We don't auto-prune dormant accounts (yet).</li>
        <li><strong>Sign-in tokens</strong> — the one-time link tokens are deleted after they're used, or expire after 10 minutes if unused.</li>
        <li><strong>Rate-limit counters</strong> — auto-reset on a 15-minute window.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">How to delete your account</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
        Email <a href="mailto:aasif@aasifj.com?subject=Delete%20my%20Policy%20Wonk%20account" class="text-[var(--color-functional-marigold)] underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80">aasif@aasifj.com</a> from the address on your account with the subject "Delete my account."
        Everything — email, nickname, avatar, play history — gets wiped within a few days. A self-serve delete button is on the roadmap; until then, this is the manual path.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Guests</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
        Play as Guest doesn't create any server-side record of you. Your in-progress game and any
        finished sessions live in your browser's <code class="font-mono text-sm">sessionStorage</code> and disappear when you close the tab.
        If you sign in later in the same tab, those completed sessions get folded into your new account's history
        so you don't lose them. After that, the local copy is cleared.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed">
        Questions, concerns, or anything that sounds off — email
        <a href="mailto:aasif@aasifj.com" class="text-[var(--color-functional-marigold)] underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80">aasif@aasifj.com</a>
        or open an issue on the
        <a href="https://github.com/criatvt/policy-wonk-game/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-functional-marigold)] underline decoration-2 underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80">GitHub repo</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--color-border)]">
      Last updated 2026-06-06.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
